# NLP Practical 2 — Bag of Words, TF-IDF, and Word2Vec

## Aim

To implement Bag-of-Words representation, normalized word counts, TF-IDF representation, and Word2Vec embeddings using a car dataset.

## Dataset

https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/CooperUnion/cardataset

The dataset contains information about different car models including manufacturer, model name, engine details, fuel type, and other attributes.

## Requirements

Python 3.x

Required libraries:
pip install pandas scikit-learn gensim numpy

## Steps

1. Load the car dataset using pandas.
2. Combine relevant text columns such as Make and Model to form sentences.
3. Convert text to lowercase.
4. Apply Bag-of-Words using CountVectorizer.
5. Calculate normalized word counts.
6. Apply TF-IDF using TfidfVectorizer.
7. Tokenize the sentences.
8. Train a Word2Vec model using gensim.
9. Extract word vectors and similarity between words.

## Expected Output

* Bag-of-Words matrix
* Normalized count matrix
* TF-IDF matrix
* Word embeddings generated using Word2Vec
* Similar words based on embedding similarity

## How to Run

python practical2.py

## Conclusion

This experiment demonstrates how textual data can be converted into numerical representations using Bag-of-Words, TF-IDF, and Word2Vec embeddings for machine learning tasks.
